minimalFix:
To fix this, the `toInternal` method in `src/mappers/ProfileMapper.ts` needs to be updated to include `avatarUrl` in the destructuring from `profile` and then assign it directly to the returned `InternalUser` object. This ensures that the avatar URL, correctly propagated by `ExternalMapper`, is not discarded.

```typescript
// src/mappers/ProfileMapper.ts
import { UserProfile, InternalUser } from '../models/UserProfile';

export class ProfileMapper {
  toInternal(profile: UserProfile): InternalUser {
    // L6: Include avatarUrl in destructuring from profile
    const { id, name, email, avatarUrl } = profile;
    // L7: Assign the correctly propagated avatarUrl to the InternalUser object
    return { id, name, email, avatarUrl };
  }

  toPublic(internal: InternalUser): Omit<InternalUser, 'id'> {
    const { name, email, avatarUrl } = internal;
    return { name, email, avatarUrl };
  }
}
```
